## Color Hierarchy & Usage Rules

### 1. Background Layer - `#606C38` (Olive Green / `brand-tertiary`)
- **Usage**: Body background only
- **Application**: `body { background: #606C38; }`
- **Purpose**: Foundation layer for entire application

### 2. Text & Typography - `#283618` (Dark Forest Green / `brand-dark`)
- **Usage**: All text, headings, labels, body copy
- **Application**: `text-brand-dark`
- **Purpose**: Primary text color with excellent contrast on cream backgrounds

### 3. Content Backgrounds - `#FEFAE0` (Cream / `brand-secondary`)
- **Usage**: Cards, forms, headers, footers, main content areas
- **Application**: `bg-brand-secondary`
- **Purpose**: Clean, readable surfaces for content
- **Examples**: Login/Register forms, Analysis form, Result cards, Headers/footers

### 4. Secondary Accents - `#DDA15E` (Golden Tan / `brand-accent`)
- **Usage**: Borders, highlights, informational elements, icons in disclaimers
- **Application**: `border-brand-accent`, `text-brand-accent`
- **Purpose**: Secondary emphasis without overwhelming
- **Examples**: Section borders, Disclaimer accents, Help box styling, Info icons

### 5. Primary Actions - `#BC6C25` (Rust Brown / `brand-primary`)
- **Usage**: Buttons, CTAs, primary interactive elements, emphasis
- **Application**: `bg-brand-primary` with `text-white`
- **Purpose**: Main call-to-action elements that demand attention
- **Examples**: Submit buttons, Primary CTAs, Important borders, Badge backgrounds

## Component Styling Rules

### Primary Content Cards
```css
bg-brand-secondary border-2 border-brand-accent rounded-lg shadow-md p-6
```
- Background: Solid cream
- Border: Golden, 2px
- Shadow: Medium depth
- Corners: Large rounded
- Purpose: Main content areas (forms, result cards)

### Disclaimer / Informational Boxes
```css
bg-brand-secondary/80 border-l-4 border-l-brand-accent border border-brand-accent/30 rounded-md p-4
```
- Background: 80% cream opacity
- Left Border: Thick golden accent bar (4px)
- All Border: Subtle golden outline (30% opacity)
- Shadow: None (flat appearance)
- Corners: Medium rounded
- Icon Color: `text-brand-accent` (golden)
- Purpose: Help boxes, AI disclaimers, informational notes
- Examples: "How Product Analysis Works", "AI-Generated Analysis"

### Special Emphasis Cards (PoC Notice)
```css
bg-brand-tertiary/30 border-2 border-brand-primary rounded-3xl shadow-md p-8
```
- Background: Olive tint (30%) for warnings
- Border: Rust, 2px
- Shadow: Medium
- Corners: Extra large rounded
- Purpose: Important notices that need attention but aren't errors

### Headers & Footers
```css
bg-brand-secondary border-b-2 border-brand-accent shadow-md
```
- Background: Cream
- Border: Bottom (or top for footer) golden, 2px
- Shadow: Medium
- Purpose: Page structure elements

### Buttons & CTAs

#### Primary Action Buttons
```css
bg-brand-primary text-white hover:bg-brand-primary/90 focus:ring-2 focus:ring-brand-primary/30
```
- Background: Rust
- Text: White
- Hover: 90% opacity
- Focus: Ring with 30% opacity
- Purpose: Main actions (submit, register, analyze)

#### Secondary/Outline Buttons
```css
border-2 border-brand-primary text-brand-primary hover:bg-brand-primary/10
```
- Background: Transparent or white
- Border: Rust, 2px
- Text: Rust
- Hover: 10% rust tint
- Purpose: Secondary actions (sign in, cancel)

#### Disabled State
```css
bg-gray-400 text-white cursor-not-allowed
```
- Use gray for disabled states

### Form Inputs
```css
bg-white border border-gray-300 focus:border-brand-primary focus:ring-2 focus:ring-brand-primary/30 text-brand-dark
```
- Background: White (NOT cream - for clarity)
- Border Default: Gray
- Border Focus: Rust
- Ring Focus: Rust with 30% opacity
- Text: Dark green

### Recommendation Badges
```css
/* Recommended */
bg-green-700 text-white border-green-900 shadow-lg
/* Used with border-2 */

/* Not Recommended */
bg-red-700 text-white border-red-900 shadow-lg
/* Used with border-2 */
```
- Recommended: Deep green background (positive, natural, clearly visible)
- Not Recommended: Deep red (universally recognized danger, earthy shade)
- Both use white text for contrast
- Border: Darker shade (green-900/red-900) for strong definition
- Border width: 2px (border-2) for balanced emphasis
- Shadow: Large (shadow-lg) for depth and separation from background

### Ingredient Concern Badges
```css
/* Unacceptable */
bg-red-700 text-white border-red-900 shadow-lg
/* Used with border (1px) */

/* Questionable */
bg-amber-600 text-white border-amber-900 shadow-lg
/* Used with border (1px) */
```
- Unacceptable: Deep red background (danger, critical issue)
- Questionable: Deep amber background (warning, caution)
- Both use white text for contrast
- Border: Darker shade (red-900/amber-900) for subtle definition
- Border width: 1px (border) for delicate emphasis - thinner than main recommendation badges
- Shadow: Large (shadow-lg) for depth and visibility
- Size: Smaller badges (xs font, less padding) as they appear inline with ingredient details

### Error States

#### Global Error Alerts
```css
bg-red-50 text-red-900 ring-red-700
```
- Light red background
- Dark red text
- Deep red border (ring)

#### Form Error Summaries
```css
