## Common Mistakes to Avoid

❌ **DON'T**:
- Use `brand-tertiary` (olive) for anything except body background
- Use brand colors for semantic states (success/error/warning)
- Add gradients (`bg-gradient-*`, `from-*`, `to-*`, `via-*`)
- Use thin borders (1px) for primary content
- Apply shadows to disclaimers
- Use rose colors for errors (use red instead)
- Forget hover/focus states

✅ **DO**:
- Use `brand-dark` for all text
- Use `brand-secondary` for all content surfaces
- Use `brand-primary` for all primary actions
- Use deep red (`red-700/800/900`) for all error states
- Add shadows to cards and forms
- Include focus states for accessibility
- Test color contrast ratios
- Keep design clean with no gradients

